parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the balancer shaft oil seal can cause the engine to lose oil suddenly, leading to engine failure, loss of power steering, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Blue and black smoke emitting from the hood area
excessive oil leaking from the engine
oil pressure light coming on
sudden loss of oil
engine shutting down
loss of power steering
heavy smoke coming from the engine compartment.
